      "en": "Tree to 20 m with white bark and hairy young twigs (unlike silver birch). Leaves more rounded than triangular, with toothed margin. Flowers April with pendulous catkins. More tolerant of wet and acidic conditions than Betula pendula. Pioneer tree in peat areas and wet heaths.",
