      "en": "Perennial 50\u2013150 cm with lance-shaped leaves and attractive pink-purple flower spikes. Flowers June\u2013August. Seed with white hair tuft, dispersed far by wind. Spectacular pioneer after wildfire or felling. Provides nectar for hummingbird hawk-moth.",
