      "en": "Perennial 30\u201380 cm with deeply cut pink petals (five 'rags'). Flowers May\u2013July. Characteristic species of species-rich, unfertilised hay meadows. Named for flowering with arrival of cuckoo. Host plant for burnished brass moths. Strongly declined due to intensification.",
