      "en": "Perennial with rosette of toothed-lobed leaves and yellow flower heads on hollow stems. Flowers almost year-round. Fruits with fluffy seed plume ('dandelion clock'). Essential for early bees in spring. Leaves edible as salad; root as coffee substitute. Name from 'dent de lion' (lion's tooth).",
